Page replacement algorithms are used in operating systems to manage memory when a page fault occurs. When a required page is not available in main memory, the system replaces an existing page based on a specific strategy.
This program simulates how pages are loaded into frames and how page faults occur based on different algorithms.
Working:
User enters number of frames.
User enters reference string (page sequence).
Pages are loaded into frames one by one.
If a page is not found in memory → page fault occurs.
If frames are full → replacement is done based on algorithm.
Total page faults are displayed at the end.
